window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Dark castles. Feudal banners. And a knightly tournament where the wrong choice could start a war.</p> <p>After the fallout in Hollyhead—and a brutal clash to reclaim Tyra’s faen birthright—Davik of Darkshire agrees to serve as gown champion for a woman he once swore to protect. His task? Choose the warrior who will win her hand—and, with luck, bury the past for good.</p> <p>But Karley is changing.</p> <p>Twisted by the spell that nearly killed her, she walks the line between what she was and what she’s becoming. Her soul pulses with arcana—and Davik can feel it scraping against the runes carved into his bones.</p> <p>Vorga, Sariel, Tyra, and Elina ride with him—fierce, loyal, and bound by the life they're forging.</p> <p>Despite promises of peace, Davik calls on the one trusted comrade he hasn't buried.</p> <p>At Windpeak, smiles are thin as banners, and daggers lie beneath silk.</p> <p>And when a dark cloud falls over the keep, secrets aren’t the only things rising from the grave.</p> <p>Magebreaker 3 is a relentless fantasy adventure of deadly betrayals, fractured promises, and bonds that refuse to break—even when they should.</p>"; 
